practitioner.about:
Dr. Hebaalah Hashem is a General Dentist in the Department of Dentistry at the Meadows branch of Medcare Medical Centre. She completed her Bachelor of Medicine and Dental Surgery from the Faculty of Oral and Dental Medicine at Ain Shams University in Cairo in Egypt. She has a certification from the American National Dental Board, too. She is an advocate of lifelong learning, evidenced by her additional certification in Nitrous Oxide Sedation.

Dr. Hashem has practised in both Egypt and UAE for many years. She worked with the Heliopolis Hospital in Cairo in Egypt for a long time before moving to the UAE to work with major healthcare providers like the Medical Services Administration of Abu Dhabi Police and the Tajmeel Specialized Medical Center (TSMC).

She is well-versed in all routine dental treatments that include caries treatment, dental fillings, root canals, gum treatment, crowns, bridges, extraction, dental implant, and fluoride treatment. She is proficient in cosmetic dentistry which includes whitening, cosmetic fillings and veneers. Her special field of interest lies in paediatric treatment under nitrous sedation. When she’s not working, she likes to unwind by cooking, swimming and shopping. She speaks Arabic and English fluently.

locations.about:
Medcare Medical Centre is a multi-specialty clinic located in Meadows Village.  Medcare Medical Centre Meadows offers the comfort care of a family with the warmth and hospitality by the highly talented and skilled medical and non-medical staff. The clinic consists of consultation rooms, laboratory and radiology facilities, Waiting area and full-fledged information kiosk with multi skilled staff trained to deal with all the requirements of the insurance based and general self-paying patients or clientele.

The services at the Medcare Medical Centre, Meadows comprises of family medicine, obstetrics and gynecology, orthopaedics, paediatrics, and dentistry.

Our network of 4 hospitals, 18 multi-specialty clinics medical centers within Dubai & Sharjah is meant to provide accessible, reliable and on-time medical care.
